## 2. `apps/` вЂ” Frontend Applications

Frontend projects that consume APIs from backend services.

### 2.1 `apps/storefront`
Customer-facing e-commerce website (Next.js).

Responsibilities:
- Home, Category (PLP), Product (PDP)
- Cart & Checkout
- Customer account
- SEO & performance

Rules:
- No direct DB access
- No supplier integration
- Uses only commerce-core APIs

---

### 2.2 `apps/admin`
Internal admin panel for operations.

Responsibilities:
- Orders management
- Imports trigger
- Pricing rules
- Catalog moderation
- RMA & refunds

---

## 3. `services/` вЂ” Backend Services

Backend business logic, APIs, and workers.

### 3.1 `services/commerce-core` (Main Backend)

This is the core API of the platform.

Responsibilities:
- Cart
- Checkout
- Orders
- Payments
- Pricing rules
- Customers
- Invoices
- Shipments
- Admin APIs

Structure:

commerce-core/
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ src/
в”‚ в”њв”Ђв”Ђ cart/
в”‚ в”њв”Ђв”Ђ pricing/
в”‚ в”њв”Ђв”Ђ common/
в”‚ в””в”Ђв”Ђ main.ts
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ prisma/
